        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 6:28PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Boyero to 19 miles southwest of
Kutch, or extending from 33 miles southeast of Limon to 46 miles
southwest of Limon, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Karval, Forder, Punkin Center, Wild Horse Point and Boyero.
</description>
